snippet.textDisplay:
Theory:

Minnie is the main character, she fell in love with a demon —soojin—, this achievement seduced and tempted her —being she an angel— that is why this song shows the process that she had to live because of this. Minnie is surrounded by other beings like her who do not let her leave where she is.

Soyeon represents minnie's soul and everything that had to happen the closer she got to the demon; their suffering, their satisfaction, their fear.
Yuqui represents the moment in which Minnie approaches Soojin, so it is seen how she runs and then is interrupted by Miyeon, who would come to be the representation of God. Yuqui later appears falling when discovered by Minnie.
shuhua represents minnie's feelings, that's why she talks about coloring herself with feelings such as red, which can represent the love she feels, and purple, which perhaps represents the fear of being discovered, but wears a majestic white dress that says what it is even though "sin" the feelings that minnie has are pure.
And finally soojin is the biggest demon in hell that tries to attract minnie to her and make her sin (that's why she holds an apple, like in the story of Adan and Eve)

To finish we see minnie in a black and white dress proven that she is nowhere to be found but still asks God for forgiveness for her sins but cannot stop loving Soojin.

At the end of it all it's just a theory. ^^

snippet.textDisplay:
A compilation theory, that is, that contains all the theories I've seen XD


*Minnie*: Human on trial. She's on one side very close to the sky. But because the "war" broke out, Minnie could not bear temptation and fear, and committed suicide, condemning her directly to hell.

Evidances: the sign Minnie makes with the gun, and the final scene where she can be seen lying in hell



*Soyeon*: Human in trial. She is also on a plane very close to heaven, only that she fell to temptation at will, not being guided by fear or anything, because of her admiration for the demon Soojin. Eventually she falls to hell, being totally deceived by Soojin. On Shuhua's part, it can be seen as she intervenes in Soojin's persuasion of this, suffering a fit of jealousy.



Evidances: The Shuhua part, the sign when she licked the barbed wire, symbolizing that she does not mind being prey to temptation, and her deep admiration for Soojin.


*Miyeon*: Goddess of purity. She was the one who put Minnie and Soyeon on trial, to see if they were able to get to heaven with her. She was the only one who did not attempt to be corrupted by Soojin, because of her elevated plane (sky), and her status.

Evidences: When she is on the raised platform (representing the sky), in that dress and that face, observing what was happening at her feet (Hell and Intermediate Plane)



*Soojin*: Queen or goddess of demons. She was the one who tempted Minnie and Soyeon, and almost Shuhua. You can see how she holds an apple, referring to the temptation that Adam and Eve suffered, and in turn, representing the devil. She ended up deceiving Soyeon primarily with what she says, "Deep in my heart" by sending her straight to hell.



Evidences: Evidence: You can see that she is in a higher office in hell, because of her dress, and because she never appeared on that red substance, representing hell. In addition to the scenes in which he emerged as a demon.


*Yuqi*: He was an angel of Miyeon, who was about to ascend to a higher office, but at one point, he was curious about what was going on with Soojin, staring, until he finally fell into temptation, and lost his position as an angel of Miyeon.



Evidences:  She can be seen walking down a rather elegant corridor, symbolizing somewhere in the sky. She was heading to a place, probably to being promoted as Angel. In another scene, you can see how she fell to low levels, blinded by the temptation that Soojin brought. It should be noted that she was not directly tempted by Soojin, she watched him from afar.


*Shuhua*: Archangel of Miyeon. Miyeon's most important angel. She promoted what Miyeon said, and she probably recruited Soyeon and Minnie. You can see how she is on the barbed wire, but not because she has fallen under soojin's power, but because it is reflected that she may even be in a dangerous situation, but because of the power she has, she will not fall. This is also observed when she was almost seduced by Soojin, proving that she cannot fight an Arcangel.
